{"source_key":"sha256-852da461b9759bc2736926d9891eb9a3","record_index":10064,"record_hash":"sha256:e1989c5af082156a8bcc1832bb149e04b655ac32e9384447f8d0adaaf957657e","timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:46:18.865Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: fc8d96\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1517\nOutput:\n- `timeline` must include enough previews and metadata to choose turns without\n  opening every turn\n- `records` must support reverse-friendly pagination with stable indexes\n- subagent/compaction/session lineage is useful, but only when the provider data\n  makes it reliable\n\nThe simulations also surfaced tempting additions that should stay out of v1:\n\n- automatic main-session selection\n- `--interesting` filters\n- generated summaries as required output\n- record-kind/path/error filtering\n- a separate `search` command\n- a combined `show` command\n\nThose are all plausible later, but they hide too much policy in the first\nversion. The primitive layer should expose enough facts for the receiving agent\nto choose, not choose for it.\n\n### Catch-Up Heuristics For The Consuming Agent\n\nThe intended agent behavior is:\n\n1. Start with `sessions branch`.\n2. Prefer recent sessions with multiple incremental turns.\n3. Treat one-turn backfills and sidecar sessions as secondary until previews\n   show they matter.\n4. Use `timeline` to find latest user corrections, assistant final/status\n   messages, tests, errors, and branch/change observations.\n5. Read `records` from the end of the most relevant turns first.\n6. Page backward or read the start of a backfill only when the current goal or\n   original instructions are unclear.\n\nThe agent should read:\n\n- exact user messages for intent and constraints\n- final/status assistant messages for claimed outcome and remaining work\n- tool calls/results for commands, tests, failures, and changed files\n- assistant prose for plans and reasoning breadcrumbs when needed\n\n## Expected Agent Access Pattern\n\nWhen a user asks an agent to catch up with a branch, the agent should not try to\nload everything. A good workflow is:\n\n1. Resolve the current branch or requested branch.\n2. Run `but agentlog sessions branch <branch>`.\n3. Pick likely useful sessions from outline data:\n   - prefer recent sessions\n\n[TRUNCATED]\ncapture kinds, and\n  highlighted turn keys.\n- The next agent should be able to distinguish main-thread work from sidecar\n  review/subagent work when that information exists. If provider metadata does\n  not expose this cleanly, the CLI should still show enough facts for the agent\n  to infer cautiously.\n- Handoff should avoid pretending related means owned. A branch can have related\n  sessions that are background review, experiments, or unrelated active\n  worktree noise.\n- We should not require GitButler app APIs for this. CLI plus `but-agentlog`\n  primitives is the right first surface.\n\n## Agent-Facing Workflow\n\nA good first workflow is deliberately small:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog sessions branch <branch>\nbut agentlog timeline <session-key> [--limit N]\nbut agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> [--from start|end|<index>] [--limit N]\n```\n\nThe exact names can change, but the shape matters:\n\n1. discover related sessions for the current target\n2. inspect a compact session/turn outline\n3. hydrate only the turns that look useful\n\nThe user prompt can be simple:\n\n```text\nCheck whether there are prior agent sessions related to this branch and catch up.\n```\n\nA future skill can teach agents this sequence, but the CLI should be sensible\nwithout the skill.\n\n## Discovery Output\n\nThe discovery command should answer:\n\n- which sessions are related to this branch/review/change?\n- which turns caused that relationship?\n- how recent are they?\n- how much data would reading them cost?\n- which agent/provider/model created them?\n- are they mostly one large backfill or incremental ongoing work?\n\nMachine-readable output should include at least:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"target_kind\": \"branch\",\n  \"target_key\": \"ref:refs/heads/example\",\n  \"sessions\": [\n    {\n      \"session_key\": \"sha256-...\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-05-20T18:12:21.645Z\",\n      \"source_count\": 1,\n      \"turn_count\": 8,\n      \"record_count\": 5785,\n      \"related_turn_keys\": [\"sha256-...\"],\n      \"agents\": [\"codex\"],\n      \"providers\": [\"openai\"],\n      \"models\": [\"gpt-5.5\"]\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:46:18.865Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}